🔹 1️⃣ WorkflowService kya hai?
👉 WorkflowService = class jo workflows ko start / manage / execute karti hai
👉 Package:-
sailpoint.api.WorkflowService
💡 Simple line me:-
👉 “Workflow chalane ka engine” = WorkflowService
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 5️⃣ Simple Example:-
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.WorkflowService;
import sailpoint.object.Workflow;

import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = SailPointContextFactory.createContext();

        WorkflowService wfService = new WorkflowService(context);

        Workflow wf = (Workflow) context.getObjectByName(Workflow.class, "My Workflow");

        Map<String, Object> argsMap = new HashMap<String, Object>();
        argsMap.put("identityName", "user1");

        wfService.launch(wf, argsMap);

        System.out.println("Workflow started...");
    }
}
🔹 6️⃣ Output:-
Workflow started...
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 1️⃣ Workflow Launch ka pura flow:-
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✔🧠 Main kaam kya karta hai?
1️⃣ Workflow Start Karna?
👉 WorkflowService ka sabse pehla kaam hota hai workflow ko start karna,
Kisi bhi workflow ko trigger karta hai
Input parameters (args) leta hai
Execution start karta hai.

👉 Example:-
WorkflowService wfService = new WorkflowService(context);
wfService.launch(workflowName, args);
--------------
✔2️⃣ Workflow Load Hota Hai:-
👉 Launch hone ke baad:-
Workflow definition DB ya XML se load hota hai
Ye ek static template/configuration hota hai
Isme steps, transitions, approvals defined hote hain
--------------
3️⃣ WorkflowCase create aur manage karna:-
Jab workflow start hota hai → ek WorkflowCase object banta hai
️⃣ WorkflowCase Me Kya Store Hota Hai
👉 WorkflowCase ke andar:-
workflow name
variables (args)
current step
status (Running / Completed / Pending)
audit info (kisne start kiya, kab, etc.)
--------------
5️⃣ Workflow Execution Control:-
👉 Ab actual execution start hota hai:-
Workflow step-by-step chalta hai
Har step ka logic execute hota hai
WorkflowService decide karta hai:
next step kya hoga (transition)
--------------
🧠 6️⃣ Variables Inject Hote Hain (Deep Explanation)
👉 Kya hota hai exactly?
Jab tu workflow launch karta hai:-
Attributes args = new Attributes();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
args.put("role", "Developer");
wfService.launch("MyWorkflow", args);
👉 Ye jo args hai na — ye hi workflow ke input variables hote hain.

⚙️ Internally kya hota hai?
✔️ Step 1: args → WorkflowCase me store
WorkflowService args ko uthata hai
Aur usko WorkflowCase ke context/variables map me daal deta hai
👉 Internally kuch aisa samajh:-
workflowCase.put("identityName", "Ravi");
workflowCase.put("role", "Developer");

✔️ Step 2: Global Variables ban jaate hain.
👉 Ab ye variables:-
Pure workflow me available hote hain
Har step me access ho sakte hain
Global scope me rehte hain
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔄 2️⃣ Workflow Execution Engine (core logic):-
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WorkflowService internally ek engine ki tarah kaam karta hai.
👉 Har step pe:-
Step identify karta hai
Step type check karta hai
Uska logic execute karta hai

🔹 Step types kya ho sakte hain:
1. Script Step
<Script>
   // Java / Beanshell code
</Script>
👉 Direct code run hota hai.

2. Approval Step:-
👉 Yaha:-
ApprovalItem create hota hai
Approver assign hota hai
Workflow pause ho jata hai

3. Task Step:-
👉 Background task run hota hai

4. Transition:-
👉 Decide karta hai:-
Next step kya hoga.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧾 3️⃣ WorkflowCase (Runtime Heart 💥):-
👉 Ye sabse critical object hai
-----------------------------------------------------
Isme kya kya hota hai:-

🔸 Basic Info:-
workflow name
case id

🔸 State:-
Running
Pending
Completed
Terminated

🔸 Variables:-
case.get("identityName");
case.put("status", "approved");

🔸 Current Step:-
Abhi kaun sa step chal raha hai
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
⏸️ 4️⃣ Pause & Resume Mechanism:-
----------------------------------------------------
👉 Jab approval aata hai:
Workflow pause ho jata hai
State → Pending
👉 Jab user approve karta hai:
WorkflowService fir se call hota hai
Workflow resume hota hai
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 5️⃣ Approval Handling (real flow):-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
👉 Internally kya hota hai:-
Approval step aaya
ApprovalItem create hua
Approver assign hua
DB me save hua
Workflow ruk gaya
👉 Approve hone pe:
approvalItem.approve();
context.saveObject(approvalItem);

👉 Fir:-
WorkflowService resume karta hai
Next step execute hota hai.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔗 6️⃣ Request + Workflow integration
----------------------------------------------------------
👉 Jab user request submit karta hai:-
Request object create hota hai
RequestDefinition decide karta hai kaunsa workflow chalega
WorkflowService launch karta hai
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔄 7️⃣ Task Integration:-
--------------------------------------------------------
👉 Workflow me task bhi run ho sakta hai:-
Identity refresh
Aggregation
Provisioning

👉 WorkflowService:-
Task trigger karta hai
Result handle karta hai
-----------------------------------------------------------------
⚠️ 8️⃣ Error Handling:-
-------------------------------------------
👉 Agar workflow me error aata hai:-
WorkflowCase me error store hota hai
Workflow terminate ho sakta hai
-----------------------------------------------------------------
🛑 9️⃣ Termination
wfService.terminate(workflowCase);
👉 Ye:-
Workflow ko force stop karta hai.
