🧠 1️⃣ getWorkflow(String name):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Workflow ko uske naam(name) se fetch karta hai,
DB ya configuration (XML) se workflow definition uthata hai.
sirf workflow(template/configuration) object deta hai.

⚙️ Internally kya hota hai:-
System workflow ka name match karta hai
Agar match mil gaya → Workflow object return
Nahi mila → null

📦 Kya return karta hai?
👉 Workflow object (template)

💡 Example:-
Workflow wf = wfService.getWorkflow("RoleAssignmentWorkflow");

👉 Ab tu:-
workflow ke steps dekh sakta hai
validate kar sakta hai
launch bhi kar sakta hai.
---------------------------------------
🧠 2️⃣ getWorkflowById(String id):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Workflow ko ID se fetch karta hai,
Usually unique identifier hota hai.

⚙️ Internally:-
DB me workflow ka ID match karta hai
Match mila → workflow return
Nahi mila → null

📦 Return:-
👉 Workflow object

💡 Example:-
Workflow wf = wfService.getWorkflowById("8a80828f123456");
-------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 1️⃣ launchWorkflow(String workflowName, Map args):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Workflow ko name se launch karta hai.
Map ke through input variables leta hai.

⚙️ Internally:-
workflowName se workflow load hota hai
Map → internally convert hota hai Attributes me
Fir actual engine launch() ko call karta hai
💡 Example:-
Map args = new HashMap();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.launchWorkflow("MyWorkflow", args);
-------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 2️⃣ launchWorkflow(Workflow workflow, Map args):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Direct Workflow object se launch karta hai,
Map input leta hai.

⚙️ Internally:-
Workflow already loaded hota hai
Map → convert hota hai Attributes me
Fir launch() call hota hai
💡 Example:-
Workflow wf = wfService.getWorkflow("MyWorkflow");
Map args = new HashMap();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.launchWorkflow(wf, args);
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 3️⃣ launch(String workflowName, Attributes args) ✅ (REAL CORE 🔥):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Ye actual core method hai.
Name se workflow load karta hai.
Direct Attributes accept karta hai.

⚙️ Internally:-
Workflow load hota hai
WorkflowCase create hota hai
Variables inject hote hain
Execution start hota hai
💡 Example:-
Attributes args = new Attributes();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.launch("MyWorkflow", args);
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 4️⃣ launch(Workflow workflow, Attributes args) ✅ (REAL CORE 🔥):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Direct Workflow object se launch karta hai
Attributes use karta hai
💡 Example:-
Workflow wf = wfService.getWorkflow("MyWorkflow");
Attributes args = new Attributes();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.launch(wf, args);
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 1️⃣ startWorkflow(String workflowName, Map args):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Workflow ko naam se start karta hai.
Map me diye gaye input variables leta hai

⚙️ Internally kya hota hai?
workflowName se workflow load hota hai
Map → convert hota hai Attributes me
Fir internally launch() method call hota hai
💡 Example:-
Map args = new HashMap();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.startWorkflow("MyWorkflow", args);
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 2️⃣ startWorkflow(Workflow workflow, Map args):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Direct Workflow object se start karta hai
Map arguments leta hai

⚙️ Internally:-
Workflow already loaded hota hai
Map → Attributes me convert
Fir launch(workflow, Attributes) call hota hai
💡 Example:-
Workflow wf = wfService.getWorkflow("MyWorkflow");
Map args = new HashMap();
args.put("identityName", "Ravi");
wfService.startWorkflow(wf, args);
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
⚠️ Important Points:-
❗ 1. Same kaam karta hai
👉 startWorkflow = launchWorkflow = wrapper

❗ 2. Real engine sirf ek hai
👉 Final execution hamesha:-
launch(...)

❗ 3. Interview trap 😈:-
Agar koi bole:-
👉 “startWorkflow aur launch me difference?”

👉 tu bol:-
startWorkflow → wrapper
launch → actual engine method

⚡ Ek Line Me:-
👉 startWorkflow internally launch ko call karta hai — direct engine method nahi hai.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 1️⃣ Concept: Resume Workflow:-
Resume ka kaam:-
Jab workflow pause ya wait state me hota hai (mostly approval, timer, external input)
Tab ye method workflow ko dobara execute state me le aata hai
Step-by-step execution wahi se continue hota hai jaha pause hua tha.

Step 0: Input Method:-
()Wrapper vs Core:-
()Wrapper call (custom project):-
wfService.resumeWorkflow(String workflowCaseId);
wfService.resumeWorkflow(WorkflowCase workflowCase);

()Core engine call:-
wfService.resume(WorkflowCase workflowCase);
wfService.resume(String workflowCaseId); // internally fetch + resume

🧠 1️⃣ Wrapper Call (Custom Project):-
Methods:-
wfService.resumeWorkflow(String workflowCaseId);
wfService.resumeWorkflow(WorkflowCase workflowCase);

Kya karte hain:-
Ye helper / wrapper methods hote hain,
WorkflowCase ko resume karne ke liye core engine (resume()) ko internally call karte hain.

()Difference bas input type me hai:-
String workflowCaseId → workflowCase ko ID se fetch karke resume karta hai
WorkflowCase object → direct object use karke resume karta hai
Execution ke har step ka logic core engine handle karta hai.

🧠 2️⃣ Core Engine Call:-
Methods:-
wfService.resume(WorkflowCase workflowCase);
wfService.resume(String workflowCaseId); // internally fetch + resume

Kya karte hain:-
Ye real workflow execution ka engine hai
Step-by-step workflow ko waha se resume karta hai jaha workflow paused / pending tha,
WorkflowCase ke variables, current step, state maintain hote hain.
Loop ke through current step → next step execute hota hai.
Status update hota hai (Running → Completed).
WorkflowCase DB / context me save hota hai aur history / audit trail update hoti hai.

()Difference from wrapper:-
Wrapper → internally call karta hai core engine,
Core engine → actual step-by-step execution logic.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 1️⃣ Suspend Workflow – Line by Line Flow:-
Scenario:-
WorkflowCase running / pending hai
Hum usko temporarily pause / suspend karna chahte hain.

()suspend(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-
ye direct Core engine hai.
Real engine method → workflow ko pause / suspended state me set karta hai.

()suspend(String workflowCaseId):-
ye Core wrapper call karta hai.
ID se WorkflowCase fetch karta hai → internally suspend(WorkflowCase) call karta hai.

()suspendWorkflow(String workflowId):-
ye Wrapper call karta hai.
ye method me→ internally core engine suspend() call karta hai.

🧠 2️⃣ Terminate Methods:-
()terminateWorkflow(String workflowId):-
Workflow ID ke basis pe workflow fetch karta hai internally aur wrapper call karta hai internally aur 
core engine ko call karta hai workflow terminate ho jaye forcefully khatam ho jaye. 

()terminate(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-
ye directly Core engine call karta hai.ki internally 
core engine → workflow ko terminate / stopped state me set karta hai.

()terminate(String workflowCaseId):-ye Core wrapper call karta hai, 
ye method ID se WorkflowCase fetch → internally terminate(WorkflowCase) call karta hai.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()🧠 1️⃣ Retry Workflow – Concept:-
Retry ka kaam:-
Jab workflow execution fail / error me ho jaye
Hum workflow ko dobara attempt karna chahte hain
WorkflowCase ke variables, current step, state maintain hote hain
Retry = fresh execution from failed step / starting point.

🔹 2️⃣ Methods Overview:-
()retryWorkflow(String workflowId):-ye method id ke basis pe workflow fetch karta hai aur 
ye Wrapper call karta hai core engine ko aur core engine internally retry(workflow) call karta hai.

()retry(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-ye method workflowCase object ka input leta hai aur directly core engine call karta hai 
aur core engine retry(workflow) method call from failed step se karta hai.

()retry(String workflowCaseId):-ye method WorkflowCase object ko ID ke basis pe fetch karta hai,
ye Core wrapper call karta hai internally core engine ko aur core engine call karta hai internally retry(workflowCaseId).
internally call retry(WorkflowCase)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()1️⃣ getWorkflowCase(String id) ✅ (Core Method):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
WorkflowCase ko ID se DB / context se fetch karta hai
🔹 Code:-
WorkflowCase wfCase = wfService.getWorkflowCase("8a80828f123456");
🔹 Internally:-
public WorkflowCase getWorkflowCase(String id) {
    return context.getObjectById(WorkflowCase.class, id); // DB se fetch
}
📌 Output:-
Ek single WorkflowCase object return
Nahi mila → null

2️⃣ getWorkflowCaseById(String id):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Same kaam as getWorkflowCase(id)
🔹 Internally:-
public WorkflowCase getWorkflowCaseById(String id) {
    return getWorkflowCase(id); // same call
}
👉 Sirf naming difference hai.

3️⃣ getWorkflowCases():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
System ke saare workflow cases fetch karta hai
🔹 Internally:-
public List<WorkflowCase> getWorkflowCases() {
    return context.getObjects(WorkflowCase.class);
}
📌 Output:-
List of all workflow cases.

4️⃣ getWorkflowCaseByName(String name) ❌ (Custom):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
WorkflowCase ko name se search karta hai
🔹 Internally (query based):-
public WorkflowCase getWorkflowCaseByName(String name) {
    QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
    qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("name", name));

    return context.getObjects(WorkflowCase.class, qo).get(0);
}

5️⃣ getWorkflowCasesByUser(String user):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Kisi specific user ke workflow cases nikalta hai
🔹 Internally:-
public List<WorkflowCase> getWorkflowCasesByUser(String user) {
    QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
    qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("owner", user));

    return context.getObjects(WorkflowCase.class, qo);
}

6️⃣ getWorkflowCasesByStatus(String status):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Status ke basis pe workflow cases filter karta hai
(Running / Completed / Pending)
🔹 Internally:-
public List<WorkflowCase> getWorkflowCasesByStatus(String status) {
    QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
    qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("status", status));

    return context.getObjects(WorkflowCase.class, qo);
}
