🧠 2️⃣ 1️⃣ saveWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase)
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Naya WorkflowCase DB me save karta hai.

🔹 Wrapper Code:-
public void saveWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase) {
    context.saveObject(workflowCase);   // DB save
    context.commitTransaction();        // commit
}

🧠 2️⃣ 2️⃣ updateWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase)
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Existing WorkflowCase ko update karta hai.

🔹 Wrapper Code:-
public void updateWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase) {
    context.saveObject(workflowCase);   // update
    context.commitTransaction();        // commit
}

🧠 3️⃣ 3️⃣ deleteWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase)
👉 Kya karta hai:-
WorkflowCase ko DB se permanently delete karta hai.

🔹 Wrapper Code:-
public void deleteWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase) {
    context.deleteObject(workflowCase); // delete
    context.commitTransaction();        // commit
}
