🧠 3️⃣ 2️⃣ getTaskById(String id):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Task ko ID se fetch karta hai
🔹 Internally:-
public Task getTaskById(String id) {
    return getTask(id); // wrapper
}

🧠 4️⃣ 3️⃣ getTask(String taskId):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Task ko direct DB / context se ID ke basis pe fetch karta hai.

🧠 2️⃣ 1️⃣ getTasks(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Ek workflowCase ke saare tasks (work items / approval tasks) nikalta hai
🔹 Internally (Query based):-
public List<Task> getTasks(WorkflowCase workflowCase) {
    QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();

    // WorkflowCase ke basis pe filter
    qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("workflowCaseId", workflowCase.getId()));

    return context.getObjects(Task.class, qo);
}
