()advance(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-
🧠 2️⃣ 1️⃣ advance(WorkflowCase workflowCase) 🔥
👉 Kya karta hai:
Workflow ko current step se next step tak execute karta hai,
Ye engine ka heart method hai,
Resume / launch ke baad internally ye hi chalta hai,
ye method Core Engine	ko call karta hai directly.
Step-by-step workflow execute karta hai.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 3️⃣ 2️⃣ complete(WorkflowCase workflowCase):-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ko final state (Completed) me le jata hai
Execution finish kar deta hai,
ye method Core Engine ko call karta hai directly.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()validateWorkflow(Workflow workflow) kya karta hai?
--👉 🔥 Ye usually launch se pehle workflow sahi hai ya nahi check karta hai.
🔹 1️⃣ Basic Validation:-
✔️ Workflow null hai ya nahi
✔️ Workflow ka naam (name) present hai ya nahi
✔️ Duplicate workflow name to nahi hai

🔹 2️⃣ Start Step Validation:-
✔️ Workflow me start step defined hai ya nahi
✔️ Start step valid step list me exist karta hai ya nahi
👉 ❌ Agar start step missing → workflow run nahi hoga.

🔹 3️⃣ Steps Validation:-
✔️ Har step ka name present hai
✔️ Step duplicate nahi hai
✔️ Step type valid hai (Script / Task / Approval / End)
✔️ Step properly defined hai (empty step nahi hona chahiye).

🔹 5️⃣ End Step Validation:-
✔️ Workflow me kam se kam ek end step hona chahiye
✔️ End step ka next step nahi hona chahiye.

🔹 6️⃣ Variables / Inputs Validation:-
✔️ Variables defined hain ya nahi
✔️ Required inputs missing to nahi hai
✔️ Variable names duplicate nahi hai
✔️ Data type compatible hai (String, Boolean, etc.).

🔹 7️⃣ Script Validation:-
✔️ Script syntax valid hai
✔️ Script null nahi hai
✔️ Required variables script me available hain
✔️ Return type sahi hai
👉 ❌ Script error → workflow fail.

🔹 8️⃣ Task Validation:-
✔️ Task definition exist karta hai
✔️ Task handler defined hai
✔️ Task properly configured hai
✔️ Required inputs available hain.

🔹 9️⃣ Approval Step Validation:-
✔️ Approver defined hai (user / role)
✔️ Approval type valid hai
✔️ Escalation / reminder config sahi hai
✔️ Approval item properly linked hai.

🔹 🔟 Condition / Rule Validation:-
✔️ Conditions valid hain (if/else)
✔️ Rule references exist karte hain
✔️ Expression syntax correct hai

🔹 1️⃣1️⃣ Loop / Flow Safety Validation:-
✔️ Infinite loop nahi hona chahiye
✔️ Circular dependency safe hai ya nahi
✔️ Workflow hang nahi hona chahiye.

🔹 1️⃣2️⃣ Metadata Validation:-
✔️ Workflow version valid hai
✔️ Description / metadata correct hai
✔️ Required flags set hain.

🧠 🔹 4️⃣ Transition Validation (Flow Check):-
👉 Ye check karta hai ki workflow ek step se dusre step tak sahi flow me ja raha hai ya nahi.

1️⃣ Next Step Exist karta hai ya nahi:-
✔️ Har step ka next step defined hona chahiye
✔️ Jo next step diya hai wo workflow me exist karta ho.

2️⃣ Dead End Check:-
✔️ Har step ka flow kisi next step ya end tak jana chahiye
✔️ Beech me rukna nahi chahiye.

3️⃣ End Step Validation:-
✔️ End step ka next step nahi hona chahiye,
✔️ Workflow properly terminate hona chahiye.

4️⃣ Circular Loop Check (Infinite Loop):-
✔️ Infinite loop avoid hona chahiye
✔️ Same steps me endlessly ghoomna nahi chahiye

5️⃣ Conditional Transition Check:-
✔️ If/Else condition valid honi chahiye
✔️ Condition ke dono paths valid step pe jane chahiye.

6️⃣ Multiple Path Validation:-
✔️ Ek step se multiple transitions ho sakte hain
✔️ Har path valid hona chahiye.

Example:-
ApproveStep:-
   → Approved → CompleteStep
   → Rejected → EndStep

7️⃣ Transition Consistency:-
✔️ Step flow logical hona chahiye
✔️ Random / unreachable steps nahi hone chahiye
❌ Error:-
Step defined hai but kisi se connected nahi ❌
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
package com.example.workflow;

import java.util.Map;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Date;

import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointFactory;
import sailpoint.object.Workflow;
import sailpoint.object.WorkflowCase;
import sailpoint.object.Task;
import sailpoint.object.QueryOptions;
import sailpoint.object.Filter;

public class WorkflowUtil {

    // =========================
    // 🔹 GET CONTEXT
    // =========================
    private SailPointContext getContext() throws Exception {
        return SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 LAUNCH WORKFLOW
    // =========================
    public WorkflowCase launchWorkflow(String workflowName, Map<String, Object> args) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        Workflow wf = context.getObjectByName(Workflow.class, workflowName);

        WorkflowCase wfCase = new WorkflowCase();
        wfCase.setWorkflow(wf);
        wfCase.setName(workflowName);
        wfCase.setVariables(args);
        wfCase.setStatus("Running");
        wfCase.setStart(new Date());

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();

        advance(wfCase);

        return wfCase;
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 RESUME
    // =========================
    public WorkflowCase resumeWorkflow(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {
        return resume(wfCase);
    }

    public WorkflowCase resume(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        if (!"Pending".equals(wfCase.getStatus()) && !"Suspended".equals(wfCase.getStatus())) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Cannot resume workflow");
        }

        wfCase.setStatus("Running");

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();

        advance(wfCase);

        return wfCase;
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 SUSPEND
    // =========================
    public void suspendWorkflow(String workflowId) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        WorkflowCase wfCase = context.getObjectById(WorkflowCase.class, workflowId);

        wfCase.setStatus("Suspended");

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 TERMINATE
    // =========================
    public void terminateWorkflow(String workflowId) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        WorkflowCase wfCase = context.getObjectById(WorkflowCase.class, workflowId);

        wfCase.setStatus("Terminated");

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 RETRY
    // =========================
    public WorkflowCase retryWorkflow(String workflowId) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        WorkflowCase wfCase = context.getObjectById(WorkflowCase.class, workflowId);

        return retry(wfCase);
    }

    public WorkflowCase retry(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        if (!"Failed".equals(wfCase.getStatus())) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Retry allowed only for failed workflow");
        }

        wfCase.setStatus("Running");

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();

        advance(wfCase);

        return wfCase;
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 GET WORKFLOW CASES
    // =========================
    public List<WorkflowCase> getWorkflowCases() throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        return context.getObjects(WorkflowCase.class);
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 SAVE / UPDATE / DELETE
    // =========================
    public void saveWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    public void updateWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    public void deleteWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        context.deleteObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 TASK METHODS
    // =========================
    public List<Task> getTasks(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
        qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("workflowCaseId", wfCase.getId()));

        return context.getObjects(Task.class, qo);
    }

    public Task getTaskById(String id) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        return context.getObjectById(Task.class, id);
    }

    public void completeTask(String taskId, Map<String, Object> args) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        Task task = context.getObjectById(Task.class, taskId);

        for (String key : args.keySet()) {
            task.setAttribute(key, args.get(key));
        }

        task.setStatus("Completed");

        context.saveObject(task);

        WorkflowCase wfCase = task.getWorkflowCase();

        context.commitTransaction();

        resume(wfCase);
    }

    public void assignTask(String taskId, String user) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        Task task = context.getObjectById(Task.class, taskId);

        task.setOwner(user);

        context.saveObject(task);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    public void reassignTask(String taskId, String user) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        Task task = context.getObjectById(Task.class, taskId);

        task.setOwner(user);

        context.saveObject(task);
        context.commitTransaction();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 HISTORY
    // =========================
    public List<String> getHistory(WorkflowCase wfCase) {
        return wfCase.getHistory();
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 VALIDATE
    // =========================
    public void validateWorkflow(Workflow workflow) {

        if (workflow == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Workflow null");
        }

        if (workflow.getStartStep() == null) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Start step missing");
        }
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 ADVANCE
    // =========================
    public void advance(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        Object step = wfCase.getCurrentStep();

        while (step != null) {
            step = null; // simplified
            wfCase.setCurrentStep(step);
        }

        complete(wfCase);
    }

    // =========================
    // 🔹 COMPLETE
    // =========================
    public void complete(WorkflowCase wfCase) throws Exception {

        SailPointContext context = getContext();

        wfCase.setStatus("Completed");
        wfCase.setCurrentStep(null);

        context.saveObject(wfCase);
        context.commitTransaction();

        wfCase.getHistory().add("Completed at " + new Date());
    }
}
